An Act in support of veterans and dependents through municipal tax bills.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Any city or town in the Commonwealth may, subject to the approvals of
2 the commissioner of revenue and the legislative body of the city or town, designate a place on its
3 municipal tax bills, or the motor vehicle excise tax bills, or mail with such tax bills a separate
4 form whereby taxpayers of the city or town can voluntarily check off, donate and pledge an
5 amount of money which shall increase the amount already due and which shall be paid over to an
6 account under the supervision of the local veterans agent for the support of veterans and
7 dependents in need.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon its passage.
